\f1\b energy
\f0\b0  industry and the latest information on Australian government initiatives. PRIUS FOR SALE: Toyota, last week, started selling the Prius, its new hybrid electric car. The four-door, five-passenger sedan runs on a 1.5-liter, 4-cylinder engine teamed with a 33-kilowatt motor. It gets about 52 miles per gallon in the city and 45 miles per gallon on the highway. The manufacturer's suggested retail price is $20,450. Toyota is adding a special eight-year, 100,000-mile warranty on all hybrid-electric components. Interested buyers must use the web site to place an order as the car is not currently for sale at Toyota dealerships. FATAL FUNGI: The Ukrainian Health Ministry said Wednesday that at least 112 Ukrainians, including 33 children, have died this year from mushroom poisoning, according to an Associated Press report. Some poisoning cases involve poisonous mushrooms mistaken for edible ones, while some of the victims appear to have gathered edible mushrooms in badly polluted areas. While the state health authorities regularly warn citizens of the dangers, mushroom collecting is a popular national pastime in summer and fall, and is for many poor Ukrainians an important means for supplementing food supplies. Seventy-four people died from mushroom poisoning in 1998 and there were 42 fatalities in 1999. MARS MOVIE: Mars passed less than one degree from the 
\f1\b sun
